race.comment: CACHINK (2) has raced well in town in strong company and third up is ready to fire. Found more like here best beaten 2L at The Heath last start stepping up to a mile. Ideally placed with the 3kg claim and has the tongue tie on for the first time. Sure to prove tough to beat. MY UNCLE DID IT (13) peaks off a nose defeat at Terang over a mile and carries 3kg less in this grade. Maps for the run of the race and has genuine claims. Stablemate SACRED EAGLE (4) didn't have the best of it at Kyneton last time, nor the one before at Dunkeld in Open company. The form prior would see him in the finish. Has a low gate and the blinkers are off again. KINGSFORD (11) is a lightly raced improver who did a big job winning a Terang Maiden from the 13 barrier. He keeps Yendall and has more up the sleeve.
